properties.desc: You've stepped into what appears to be the Heniz center of commerce.
You find yourself in a room surrounded by trees with somewhat-ripe apples on them. The smell is neither pleasant nor unpleasant.
You find yourself in a room of trainers, cramped for space and holed up together.
You find yourself near the border of a clearly war-torn battlefield.
You find yourself near the border of a clearly war-torn battlefield.
You see around you a wasteland of bodies, some dead, some undead. No man comes out of here alive.
You kick the dirt aside and see a more obvious hole in the ground, covered up by leaves. Watch your step.
You find yourself in a hand-carved passageway beneath the surface. It's dark and could lead anywhere.
From the top of the stairs, your senses are blown apart by the putrid smell below.
You step through the gates and see a wondrous city inside of the castle.
You see in front of you a gigantic castle.
The citizens here sure like their fountains and apple trees.
You see a hidden grove of apple trees.
You've stumbled upon a secret community of separatists from the faction war.
You've stepped into a bustling shop.
You wonder what must be behind that door in a building like this.
The local encruster seems to be doing well for himself, based on the regal rug he has here.
The warm glow of the smith's building strikes you all at once as you open the door.
This must be the only place comfortable enough to sleep in this village.
This room smells slightly less pungent than the remainder of the surrounding bog, a sign that the leader of the Heniz resides here.
You see in front of you the Royal king of the Steffen. The atmosphere in the room is daunting.
You see here a bunch of unmarked graves. So many Heniz killed for such a trite cause...
Here lies General Lugrin, Heniz Warhero.
You see here a bunch of unmarked graves. So many Steffen killed for naught...
Here lies General Sedgwick, Steffen Warhero.
You find yourself in a peaceful homlet surrounded by walls. This small town must have enlisted the Steffen to help prevent casualties.
Here lies Lieutenant Dragh, Steffen Warhero.
Here lies Lieutenant Taheu, Steffen Warhero.
Here lies Lieutenant Blazer, Steffen Warhero.
Here lies Lieutenant Matrim, Steffen Warhero.
Here lies Lieutenant Blackmoore, Steffen Warhero.
You wade through dark, dirty tunnels for what seems like hours and find yourself in a small, lit clearing.
You enter a building that has a lot of objects strewn about. It looks like a storage room.
You find yourself in a room with a man who clearly has some authority. His eyes meet yours as you enter.
You find yourself in a room with a man who clearly has some authority. His eyes meet yours as you enter.
You enter a building that has a lot of objects strewn about. It looks like a storage room.
As you enter the hut, you see a lot of ancient pieces of equipment. Where did all these come from?
You feel an overwhelming sense of dread as the flow of magic gets stronger.
